                <Header>History</Header>
                <Paragraph>On April 2, 1792, the U.S. Congress passed the Coinage Act, establishing the first national mint in the United States. Over two centuries later, one of the Federal Government's oldest agencies continues to serve the American public. To learn more about the U.S. Mint, visit its "History" web page.</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
